            <thetext>At the moment the Iframe includes a mixin for using overflow to hide native scroll-bars, but this has only an effect on Firefox. Other Browsers ignore the the CSS property for Iframes and the scroll-bars are always visible when the content exceeds the specified height/width. 

The only possibility to implement a cross browser behavior is to use the attribute &quot;scrolling&quot;, but this attribute doesn&#39;t differentiate between the x and y axis. So the current overflow API is incompatible with the new needed behavior.

-&gt; The overflow API should be deprecated and a new property for configuring the scrolling behavior is needed.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
